Prerequisites
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Perl >= 5.8 (http://perl.org)

* Config::Tiny/2.12           * BerkeleyDB/0.34
* WWW::Curl/4.05              * URI::Escape/3.29
* HTML::TokeParser/2.37       * Clipboard/0.09 (optional)
* IO::Pager/0.05 (optional)   * XML::Simple/2.18
* Expect/1.21 (optional)

Most distros should have the above versions available as packages.
If not, you can still use CPAN to install the missing modules, e.g.:
    % cpan install WWW::Curl # as root


Installation
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Extract:
    % tar xvjf clive-$release.tar.bz2; cd clive-$release

Run:
    % ./clive [option]... [URL]...

Getting started:
    % ./clive --manual

The manual page is written in Perl Pod markup language and it is embedded
in the script file. See "perldoc perlpod" for more info. For example:
    % pod2man clive > clive.1
    Or:
    % ./genman # Wraps the above with some of the most common options

See also:
    configrc file which serves as an example configuration file


Installation: FreeBSD
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

These details apply to FreeBSD 7.0 fresh-outta-box. The ports tree is
the same installed from the CD1 before updating it.

From Ports:
-----------

 * databases/p5-BerkeleyDB
 * textproc/p5-XML-Simple
 * security/p5-Digest-SHA
 * devel/p5-Config-Tiny
 * devel/p5-Date-Manip
 * devel/p5-Parse-Yapp
 * textproc/p5-XML-DOM
 * devel/p5-IO-Tty
 * www/p5-libwww
 * net/p5-URI

From CPAN:
----------

 * WWW::Curl (% cpan install WWW::Curl # as root)
   - The ports (www/p5-WWW-Curl) is still 3.02 and outdated

   - depends on ExtUtils::MakeMaker which is available also as
   devel/p5-ExtUtils-MakeMaker but cpan insisted installing from CPAN

   - freshports.org listed the latest version of ExtUtils::MakeMaker
   available in the ports but I did not try it
     


Installation: Ubuntu (Hardy)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Likely inaccurate.

From apt: # Typically: "sudo apt-get install $module"
  * libcurl4-openssl-dev # Required to build WWW::Curl 4.05 using CPAN
  * libhtml-parser-perl
  * libconfig-tiny-perl
  * libberkeleydb-perl
  * libdigest-sha-perl
  * libxml-simple-perl
  * libfile-spec-perl
  * liburi-perl 
  * perl-doc
  -- Optional:
  * libexpect-perl
  * xclip (for Clipboard module below)

From CPAN: # Typically: "sudo cpan install $module"
  * WWW::Curl
  -- Optional:
  * IO::Pager
  * Clipboard
